text: S. Camille Solis (born 16 November 1971) is a former road cyclist from Belize. She represented her nation at the 1992 and 1996 Summer Olympics in the women's road race. She was the first woman to represent Belize at the Olympics. ==References== Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:Belizean female cyclists Category:Cyclists at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Cyclists at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic cyclists of Belize Category:Cyclists at the 1995 Pan American Games Category:Pan American Games competitors for Belize Category:Cyclists at the 1994 Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for Belize Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
